DOCUMENT();      

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

##############################################################
#  Setup

$mc = new_checkbox_multiple_choice();
$mc -> qa (
  "Check all that apply.", 
  "ODE",
  "linear",
  "system",
);
$mc -> extra(
  "autonomous",
  "PDE"
);


##############################################################
#  Text

BEGIN_TEXT
Consider
\[
\frac{dx}{dt} = 3x-2y , \qquad 
\frac{dy}{dt} = 5x-t y .
\]
\{ $mc -> print_q() \}
$BR
\{ $mc -> print_a() \}
$PAR
$BITALIC $BBOLD Book: $EBOLD
\{ htmlLink("https://www.jirka.org/diffyqs/html/classification_section.html", "Section 0.3 of Notes on Diffy Qs") \}
$EITALIC
END_TEXT

##############################################################
#  Answers

install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mc->correct_ans() ) );

##############################################################

BEGIN_SOLUTION
There are two equations, and so this is a system of equations.
There is only one independent variables, \(t,\) 
and so it is an ODE and not a PDE.
The dependent variables and their derivatives (the \(x,\) \(y,\) \(\frac{dx}{dt},\) and \( \frac{dy}{dx} \))
only appear linearly,
and in no other functions or powers, so it is linear.
$PAR
It is also not autonomous since it does
depend on \(t,\) in particlar the term \(ty.\)
END_SOLUTION

##############################################################

COMMENT("Classify an ODE system (check all that applies, nonrandomized).");

